      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:6:6:83:4",
      "text": [
        " إِذَا بَلَغَ الرَّجُلُ خَمْسِينَ سَنَةً فَلَا يَبِيتَنَّ وَ فِي جَوْفِهِ شَيْ‏ءٌ مِنَ السَّمْنِ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Ibn Abu Umeyr, from Hammad Bin Usman, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘When the man reaches fifty years, so he should not go to sleep and inside him is something from the margarine’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "4. Ali ibn Ibrahim has narrated from his father from ibn abu ‘Umayr from Hammad ibn ‘Uthaman who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ‘When a man becomes fifty years old he must not go to sleep with an amount of ghee in his stomach.’” "
        ]
      }
    },
